{
  "hosting": {
    "public": ".",
    "ignore": [
      "firebase.json",
      "**/.*",
      "**/node_modules/**",
      "README.md"
    ],
    "rewrites": [
      {
        "source": "**",
        "destination": "/index.html"
      }
    ]
  }
}
```

4. **Commit the file**

This configuration tells Firebase:
- `"public": "."` - Deploy files from the root directory (where your index.html is)
- `"ignore"` - Don't deploy these files
- `"rewrites"` - Send all requests to index.html (useful for single-page apps)

